eenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Most potentially potent dueling factor</span><hr size=1> For duelling either caster to caster or melee to caster the single most powerful prefight preparation is magic resistance.  Duels seldom pan out to be just who can do more damage faster,  in fact they often turn into battles of who can prevent you from damaging them while they pummel you.  A nice high magic rsisstance is like life insurance or life assurance if you will,  it all but guarantees  that you will have every opportunity to dish out the damage you are capable of.  Examples of the utility are preventing things like fear, blind, stuns, root, mesmerization, snare and any other severely debilitating spells.  Also keep in mind that there are spells designed to lower your resistances and all of them have to get past your magic resist stat before they can apply to other stats.  In essence all classes should be on nearly equal footing if you can prevent these kindas of situations i.e. rooted, snared, feared etc.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#353535><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Abbyss</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>   <font color=#FF0000>(9/25/00 5:15:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbloodcirclefrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> When fighting against pet owning classes </span><hr size=1> Many people will waste alot of the fight trying to get rid of the pet by rooting fearing it etc.  My advice is to forge the pet,  The pet owenrs are without exception far more dangerous than the pet and in an actual duel (not arena) when the owner bites it so does the pet.  Pets by nature are warriors and they come with a warriors natural resists making them difficult at best to get out of the way.  Don't be like all the other fools kill the master and you have won anyhow, afterall who in their right mind would say oh you may have killed me but not my pet... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1E1E1E><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/uharrisonabbeyroad1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Harrison AbbeyRoad1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/26/00 9:32:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbloodcirclefrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Most potentially potent dueling factor</span><hr size=1> Casters...Bah !!!!<br>
<br>
Well...being the wussy that I am....I will never challenge a caster to a duel.<br>
<br>
However, I do remember a time when a 20 something Ranger beat a 30 something Wiz in the arena in FreePort by not letting the Wiz mez. Ranger's and thier arrows!!!<br>
<br>
I will not mention any names....<br>
&lt;cough&gt; Giljorak &lt;cough&gt; Intuity. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#353535><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/uerylflynn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eryl Flynn</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Real Slim Shady</span><br>  Posts: 330<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/28/00 3:47:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbloodcirclefrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.dimensional.com/~malekith/ef1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Most potentially potent dueling factor</span><hr size=1> As the channeling skill grows arrows are less likely to interutp, plus how many ice comets at 49 will it take to kill you?  With luck Harrison you might take a wiz, but you need to have LoH, stuns ready, bash ready and some luck.  Buff your MR so he can't root you, if you can root him.  When he goes to cast bash or cast stun him.  If you hit hard and fast you may win.  Dispell is nice also, at 50 they have 200hp about from sheilding and that if done first makes you dispell a 200 point nuke. <p>Eryl Flynn Level 47 Wood Elf Bard on Prexus
<P>

<img src=http://www.dimensional.com/~malekith/ErylThongSong.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1E1E1E><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/usileena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sileena</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/29/00 5:26:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbloodcirclefrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Most potentially potent dueling factor</span><hr size=1> OK I have to post here in defense of wizards...<br>
<br>
We are by far...the worst duelers in the game after level 30 or so...<br>
<br>
Any time I've attempted to duel a warrior I've got my butt handed too me.  At least...in closed space environments...haven't tried open door yet.  <br>
<br>
Reason 1: High Magic Resistance.  As a wizard I have 2 utility spells to save my butt...Root and Stun both of which are resisted.  When I'm in closed doors I'm normally in a dungeon so I don't use Yonder but I haven't tried in in an outdoor situation.  <br>
<br>
Reason 2: Highly interrupted.  Most warriors now a days have a delay of roughly 15 or so.  I mean with an FBSS or what ever Haste item they are toting they have a very low delay and interrupt upon impact quite frequently.<br>
<br>
Here's how I see it for a wizard:<br>
<br>
Wizard vs Melee = Melee Winner<br>
<br>
Wizard vs Caster = Wizard Winner<br>
<br>
(BTW...Mage pets are easy to get rid of...just root them and focus on the caster =P)<br>
<br>
Anyway that's my 2cp on the matter...<br>
<br>
Sil --- out!<br>
<br>
