<br>
Mage shock spells interupt casting.  I think mages get an endure magic line and a smart one casts that on the pet.  IE no root.  BUT once you get lures and draughts post 50 I think the wiz can dual a warrior and possibly win. <p>Eryl Flynn Level 47 Wood Elf Bard on Prexus
<P>

<img src=http://www.dimensional.com/~malekith/ErylThongSong.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1E1E1E><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Abbyss</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>   <font color=#FF0000>(9/30/00 7:56:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbloodcirclefrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Wizards In duels </span><hr size=1> From what I have seen with Intuity going to town in the pit he seems to do exactly the opposite.  He owns all the tanks but gets jacked by most casters especially those with pets.  Even though root may be had to get off on a warrior it only takes one success and you can blow em apart at high levels.  The pet root thing works at lower levels but once you get a high end pet and cast magic resist on them they become even harder to root than the warrior.  One thing that scares me about wizards are the new Lure line of spells them things got like a 3 second cast time and IMHO put the wizard back into the game in a major way by allowing them to just mash buttons and probably still get off the spells with a pet or person beating on them.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#353535><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/usinyan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sinyan</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/2/00 8:10:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbloodcirclefrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards In duels </span><hr size=1> If your a melee dueling a caster and you like to fight dirty like myself then one way to take the pet out of the equation is to give him a rusty dagger or rusty sword before you challenge the caster to a duel. This way if he does hit you it won't hurt as bad and not as often <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center>~Sinyan~</center><br>
<center>-Level 26 DE Warrior-</center>
<center><img src="http://www.facelink.com/edit/raw/image/23/2261623.jpg"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1E1E1E><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/uerylflynn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eryl Flynn</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Real Slim Shady</span><br>  Posts: 337<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/3/00 5:11:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbloodcirclefrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.dimensional.com/~malekith/ef1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards In duels </span><hr size=1> Sinyan, giving a pet a weapon only effects the pet if the weapon is faster and less damage than the weapon they are using.  A while back a change was made, pets use their damage or the weapons which ever is better and the weapon does nothing to effect the attack delay of the pet.  What this means is before a pet dual weilds you can make the pet hit for less if they had a good weapon like a halberd or 2 hand sword.  But by the time they dual weild you can't change the damage they do by much like this. <p>Eryl Flynn Level 48 Wood Elf Bard on Prexus
<P>

<img src=http://www.dimensional.com/~malekith/ErylThongSong.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#353535><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ualkerionfyrewalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alkerion Fyrewalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/3/00 1:38:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbloodcirclefrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards In duels </span><hr size=1> Just to throw my 2cp in on this mess as well.  I've dueled a 52 ranger dual wielding a revultant whip and a lupine dagger.  He has soome sort of haste item on.  Even with me using the lure line to guarantee full damage for mana (Which BTW takes 6 seconds to cast lure, not 3) I still ended up beating him with about 20 hp to spare.<br>
<br>
On a side note on that one, I had challenged him to the duel, he didn't accept or reject the offer, and waited till he was fully ready and standing BEHIND me to start the duel.  Even with all that I still beat him.  My wizaard was 53 at the time.<br>
<br>
I took on a 51 or 52 warrior after that and it turned into a LONG drawn out affair of nuke/yonder cause his MR was WAY too high for me to land root on.  That combined with the fact that I was still using lures (which use up like 320 mana for 640 damage.  1 to 2 ratio versus the 1/3 and better ratios of IC and the draught line of spells) spelled my doom in that battle.<br>
<br>
BTW, any wizzy that duels a warrior inside of a dungeon, or any other tight confined space might as well nuke himself to death.  Not gonna win that one without that ability to put some distance between you and the tank.   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
